cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.AI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the role of machine learning in high-performance computing and presents memory packing techniques to optimize decision forests. It may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as decision forests are trivially parallelizable and the paper discusses parallelization techniques. Additionally, it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it discusses the traversal of tree data structures and memory access patterns. It may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as decision forests are commonly used in image classification tasks. Finally, it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as decision forests are a popular machine learning technique.
